clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: For the treatment of bronchospasm due to asthma emphysema and chronic bronchitis

contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Aminophylline is the ethylenediamine salt of theophylline Theophylline stimulates the CNS skeletal muscles and cardiac muscle It relaxes certain smooth muscles in the bronchi produces diuresis and causes an increase in gastric secretion
